Please see http://www.zabbix.com/ for detailed information about Zabbix.
On-line Zabbix documentation is available at http://www.zabbix.com/documentation/2.0/manual/installation/install .


In order to monitor jboss-7 you would require following libs under zabbix_java/lib.

jboss-as-jmx-7.1.3.Final.jar
jboss-as-logging-7.1.3.Final.jar
jboss-as-remoting-7.1.3.Final.jar
jboss-logging-3.1.2.GA.jar
jboss-logmanager-1.3.2.Final.jar
jboss-marshalling-1.3.15.GA.jar
jboss-marshalling-river-1.3.15.GA.jar
jboss-remote-naming-1.0.4.Final.jar
jboss-remoting-3.2.8.SP1.jar
jboss-sasl-1.0.3.Final.jar
jcl-over-slf4j-1.6.1.jar
jul-to-slf4j-stub-1.0.0.Final.jar
log4j-jboss-logmanager-1.0.1.Final.jar
logback-classic-0.9.27.jar
logback-console.xml
logback-core-0.9.27.jar
logback.xml
org-json-2010-12-28.jar
remoting-jmx-1.0.4.Final.jar
slf4j-api-1.6.1.jar
xnio-api-3.0.6.GA.jar
xnio-nio-3.0.6.GA.jar

Reconfigure zabbix as 

./configure --enable-server --enable-agent --with-mysql --with-libcurl --with-libxml2 --enable-java
make install


